        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 3:33PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 332 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Briscoe, or 19 miles southeast of Miami, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Briscoe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
